\par\par \b \uc2  Stocks tumble almost 5% to a six year low. \b0\par\par\uc2 705 \uc2 words\par \uc2 19 September 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  9 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Share prices on the Jakarta Stock Exchange plunged further yesterday with the main price gauge falling to a six-year low. \par \par \uc2  But the rupiah remained stable at the 11,000 level despite the share price plunge. \par \par \uc2  Securities analysts attributed the continued drop in share prices on strong rumors that the government would impose a foreign exchange control. \par \par \uc2  Fears of the imposition of a capital control remained strong despite a government denial, one analyst said, adding that a \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  circular issued to banks about withholding \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  on gains from interest on \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  promissory notes in the morning added to fears of a forex curb. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  stressed Friday that foreigners could still buy its notes, provided they pay a \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Offshore investors can only benefit from the exemption if they enclose a statement from the \b \highlight22\uc2 taxation\b0 \highlight\uc2  department of their own country, stating that they are a legal entity incorporated in a country that has a \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2 -exemption treaty with Indonesia, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  said. \par \par \uc2  "Market fear of a capital control has not diminished ... so most investors are trying to cash in stocks they hold here," Andre Cita, associate director of state-owned securities firm Bahana Securities, said. \par \par \uc2  Fear of a global recession and the worsening of the corporate financial performance also remains a major problem in stock trading. \par \par \uc2  Andre said that most investors suspected that emerging markets were on edge of collapse, thereby forcing them to shun the market immediately to cut losses. \par \par \uc2  "It is just like a roller coaster, most investors are dumping all the stocks they have," an institutional dealer with Trimegah Securindo Lestari said. \par \par \uc2  She said that most foreign brokerage firms operating in the local market such as Jardine Fleming, ING Barings, ABN Amro and Vickers Ballas Tamara were on the selling side for the whole trading day. \par \par \uc2  The JSX Composite Index fell 4.84 percent or 13.80 points to a six-year low of 271.67 on Friday with a total turnover of 167.91 million shares worth Rp 177.45 billion (US$16.18 million). \par \par \uc2  Losers led gainers 71 to 15 with 91 stock remaining unchanged. \par \par \uc2  The main price index in the local exchange has lost by almost 33.74 percent compared to 410.01 at the beginning of the trading this year and by 63.32 percent compared to 740.83 on July 8 last year when the crisis began to hit the country. \par \par \uc2  The head of research at BNI securities, Adrian Lesmana, said on Friday that almost all factors were discouraging for stock trading. \par \par \uc2  He said that with political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  at home, combined with a shrinking \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the high interest rate \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  adopted by the government, investors had no reason to stay in the market. \par \par \uc2  "With \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  at over 60 percent in time deposits, investors prefer to put their funds in the banking system for a higher yield," he said, adding that portfolio investment in money market instruments were much safer than in the equity market now. \par \par \uc2  Trading activities were marred by the suspension of PT Hanson Industri Utama and PT Wahana Jaya Perkasa after the former's stock price experienced a significant increase and the latter's experienced a drastic fall. \par \par \uc2  Unlike the stock market, the rupiah remained stable against the U.S. dollar in thin trading on Friday at a lack of fresh leads ahead of the weekend. \par \par \uc2  "But there are almost no transactions," said a dealer with Bank Niaga, Robert Z Toruan, pointing that offshore investors usually took profits ahead of the weekend to square their positions. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah, which opened at 11,200, fell to 11,300 at midday before ending Friday's trading at 11,200 to the American dollar in the Jakarta spot market on Friday. \par \par \uc2  Dealers said that market fears of possible social and political instability at home had prevented offshore operators from entering the market. \par \par \uc2  "Who will build new positions when there is no fresh news to justify new positions?" Niaga's Robert said. \par \par \uc2  Dealers, however, said the rupiah was expected to trade within a tight range next week as the market was still affected by escalating student demonstrations. (aly) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924du9j0062b\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
