\par\par \b \uc2  Economist warns fair election difficult in  \highlight22\uc2 economic \highlight\uc2  crisis. \b0\par\par\uc2 474 \uc2 words\par \uc2 2 October 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  2 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Noted senior economist Sarbini Sumawinata said it was hard to imagine the realization of fair and free elections in the midst of widespread difficulties in buying inexpensive food. \par \par \uc2  Antara quoted him on Thursday as saying that \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery should be the main agenda at least until the end of the year. \par \par \uc2  "Elections don't necessarily mean building as many political parties as possible, but it requires people to be prepared," he told a discussion in Surabaya. "Would the people be able to survive until the end of 1998?" he said. \par \par \uc2  "If things get worse, given the estimate by the ILO (International Labor Organization) of 140 million poor people, two out of three people will be poor, so a fair election would be difficult to realize," Sarbini said, referring to elections slated for May 1999. \par \par \uc2  The ILO had predicted in its report last month that without any improvement in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  about 140 million or 66 percent of the population will be living below the poverty line. \par \par \uc2  Observers have raised concern of the increasingly higher potential of vote buying particularly targeting the poor. \par \par \uc2  Mulyana W. Kusumah, secretary general of the Independent Election Monitoring Committee (KIPP), said on Wednesday that one constraint in drawing up a work schedule for election monitoring was the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  of the timing of elections given the crisis. \par \par \uc2  Following a conference on election monitoring, Mulyana said on Thursday that 847,000 volunteers were needed to cover 420 districts in the elections. \par \par \uc2  Mulyana was referring to districts as defined by the government draft law on elections, deliberation on which is scheduled to begin at the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  on Friday. \par \par \uc2  Among others, districts based on regencies from which legislators are elected have at the most 600,000 voters. \par \par \uc2  In last year's elections 124.7 million voters were registered, of which 110.9 million voted. The Committee said it still had the support of 9,000 volunteers in 47 cities and 14 provinces from last year's election and said at the most it would be able to gain 50 percent of the needed 847,000 volunteers. \par \par \uc2  Jakarta residents who are interested in participating as volunteers can register at KIPP's headquarters in Rawamangun, East Jakarta (Tel: 489-5982), Mulyana said. \par \par \uc2  Given KIPP's limited expectations of recruiting enough volunteers, Mulyana said other independent bodies might be needed to monitor the elections and also in the management of hundreds of thousands of volunteers. \par \par \uc2  KIPP, he said, started to recruit new volunteers last month. In Jakarta, 100 people registered within a month. \par \par \uc2  Among current programs, Mulyana said, until December this year KIPP, set up in 1996, was preparing educational programs for voters and studying more about political parties as part of its efforts to raise \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  political awareness. (01) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924dua2006h4\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
