\par\par \b \uc2  Freedom of expression bill submitted. \b0\par\par\uc2 510 \uc2 words\par \uc2 3 October 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  agreed on Friday to deliberate a controversial bill regulating freedom of expression, after rejecting earlier this week an emergency government \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  in lieu of a law. \par \par \uc2  Deputy House Speaker Hari Sabarno told a plenary session after receiving the bill from the government - represented by Minister of Justice Muladi - that House Commission I for political affairs was assigned to deliberate the bill. \par \par \uc2  On the bill's intent, Muladi told legislators: "This draft bill does not restrict the freedom (of expression in \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 ), or reduce the freedom, much less forbid it, but it ensures the effectiveness of \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  expression of opinion and guarantees \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  security and order." \par \par \uc2  Muladi said it was not meant to impinge on the rights and fundamental freedoms of people, but to guarantee respect for the rights of others. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Public\b0 \highlight\uc2  expression of opinion, he added, was also regulated in other countries, including democratic ones. \par \par \uc2  "It's ... more regulatory than repressive," he said. \par \par \uc2  The draft law remains substantially similar to the emergency bill - sponsored by the Ministry of Defense - that the government withdrew on Tuesday following heavy \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  protest. \par \par \uc2  It still requires organizers of \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  demonstrations, protests and rallies to provide detailed notification to the police three days in advance. \par \par \uc2  Details must include the objectives of the gathering, the venue, itinerary, time of commencement and duration, names and addresses of the individuals or groups organizing the action, equipment used and the number of participants. \par \par \uc2  A police permit is required for demonstrations involving more than 100 people. The emergency bill had demanded the same permit for a demonstration of more than 50 people. \par \par \uc2  Police should issue a permit 48 hours after receiving the application at the latest, and the rally or demonstration can only be held 72 hours afterward, the draft states. \par \par \uc2  The revoked bill - called Perpu No. 2/1998 - did not require endorsement by the House to go into effect, but the body is entitled to revoke it and thus render it void. \par \par \uc2  The replacement bill requires endorsement, and a lengthy debate process which the emergency bill would have avoided. \par \par \uc2  Muladi argued the draft bill, if passed, would be "very helpful in overcoming the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain public\b0 \highlight\uc2  order and security situation, including in the national \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , and is also hoped to be able to restore \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  confidence here and abroad on the upholding of the law in Indonesia". \par \par \uc2  He said a consideration in submitting the bill had been that "practices and methods of \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  expression of opinion were often accompanied by acts causing material and other losses". \par \par \uc2  The first emergency bill had been introduced after the fall of former president Soeharto on May 21 amid mounting \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  pressure, street rallies and violent riots. \par \par \uc2  Critics, including human rights groups, had called on the House not to pass the first bill and for the government to revoke it, saying it restricted freedom of expression guaranteed by the 