\par\par \b \uc2  Unemployment threat hangs over everyone. \b0\par\par\uc2 639 \uc2 words\par \uc2 4 October 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  If it could happen to nearly 20 million of us, then the assumption holds that the ax of redundancy could fall on you. Losing one's job is now a real and frightening prospect for nearly all Indonesians. In this week's cover story, The Jakarta Post team of reporters - Aloysius Unditu, Johannes K. Simbolon, Ridwan M. Sijabat, Sri Purwati, Stevie Emilia, IGN Oka Budhi Yogaswara and Lukman Natanagara - looks into the issue of unemployment. \par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): For millions of people, the writing had long been on the wall. \par \par \uc2  Still, when the dreaded pink slips actually arrived, most were at a loss as to what tomorrow held. \par \par \uc2  In a protracted \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis with no end in sight, a bleak and daunting future loomed for the majority. \par \par \uc2  Government statistics show 18 million people are currently out of work, with the number to increase to 20 million by the end of the year. Of course, there is the necessary qualifier that government figures tend to grossly underestimate the actual number of unemployed. \par \par \uc2  The process of losing one's job is traumatic even before the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  of the loss of a regular income sets in. \par \par \uc2  It can be doubly stressful when fired workers become locked in long disputes with their employers over what they consider their entitlements. \par \par \uc2  Sri Wahyuni left high school in 1989 and went straight into a job as a flight attendant at Mandala Airlines. She enjoyed the work because of the extensive travel and the people she met. \par \par \uc2  All that changed on June 11. \par \par \uc2  "I didn't suspect anything when I received a letter asking me to attend a meeting at headquarters," Yuni, as she is known to her friends, recounted. \par \par \uc2  It was the end of the line for her and 10 colleagues, but their battle for adequate severance pay had only just begun. \par \par \uc2  Yuni recalled that management representatives offered a straight cash payment, without taking into account the years of their service. \par \par \uc2  About 40 laid-off Mandala employees turned to the Jakarta Legal Aid Institute (LBH) and the Ministry of Manpower for help to obtain their rightful benefits, including full salary payments, which had been cut in half since February. \par \par \uc2  With help from LBH and several \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  protests, they won their case eventually. \par \par \uc2  Complaints \par \par \uc2  Head of LBH Jakarta's labor division Surya Tjandra said the institute received about 300 complaints from 7,500 dismissed workers between August 1997 and August 1998. \par \par \uc2  "These cases were usually disputes over severance pay," Surya said, recalling that most companies argued they were unable to make payments because of the crisis. \par \par \uc2  Half of all the cases handled by LBH were settled, he added. \par \par \uc2  Yuni now attends a college in Jakarta, a path also chosen by some of her fired colleagues. Others have taken up teaching jobs at kindergartens or started their own businesses. \par \par \uc2  The less fortunate are still job hunting. \par \par \uc2  The spirit may be willing, but pounding the pavement and making the office rounds in search of work can be frustrating. \par \par \uc2  Job seekers cannot turn to an organized labor exchange system, providing detailed information on vacancies. \par \par \uc2  The Ministry of Manpower attempted to run such an exchange through its branches in each province, but the system broke down because of lackluster participation from private companies. \par \par \uc2  Ministry spokesman Sri Harto said a 1981 law requires companies to inform the Ministry of Manpower of any available positions and recruitment plans. \par \par \uc2  The rule was virtually ignored for the last decade as companies preferred to recruit directly, such as through advertisements in newspapers. \par \par \uc2  Sri Harto said that ideally the \b \highlight22\uc2 regulation\b0 \highlight\uc2  should be enforced to allow the ministry to steer the jobless to suitable jobs. \par \par \uc2  For the growing ranks of the unemployed, enforcement of the rule could hold one of the few glimmers of hope amid the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  gloom. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924dua4006np\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  BI-40 down 46.49% in third quarter. \b0\par\par\uc2 266 \uc2 words\par \uc2 5 October 1998\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (Bisnis): 40 prime shares that make up the BI-40 in the third quarter of 1998 dropped drastically by 51.205 points (46.49%) from 110.144 to 58.321. \par \par \uc2  The drop is slightly larger than that suffered by the LQ-45 index, which fell 47.206 points (46.47%) to 53.724 from 101.592 three months earlier. \par \par \uc2  Within the same time span the JSX composite index (IHSG) plunged by 169.770 points (38.07%) from 445.920 (30/06) to 276.150 (30/09). \par \par \uc2  The fall was due to selling pressure by investors on blue chip shares as a result of the prolonged monetary crisis which caused many issuers to perform badly. \par \par \uc2  High \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  and runway inflation, compounded by the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  situation have made the bourse less buoyant than before. \par \par \uc2  Market incentives such as IMF's loan disbursement, the CGI US$7.9 billion aid, the ADB loan of US$300 million, rescheduling of government d