\par\par \b \uc2  Hotel industry showing sign of slow recovery. \b0\par\par\uc2 697 \uc2 words\par \uc2 10 October 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  8 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The hotel industry's sluggish post-riot period has shown signs in the last two months of coming to an end, with occupancy rates climbing to above 40 percent from less than 20 percent during the first half of the year. \par \par \uc2  Hoteliers attributed the improvement in the industry to the relatively stable \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  conditions and political situation over the last two months. \par \par \uc2  They said that despite the country often being rocked by on-again, off-again street demonstrations, the situation had been very encouraging lately as business activities in the capital had started to pick up again. \par \par \uc2  "Our occupancy rate has been improving to between 30 percent and 40 percent since August as many people are coming back to the country to continue their businesses. Some big international companies have held meetings here," the Jakarta Hilton's \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  relations executive Dewi Widiyanti told The Jakarta Post on Friday. \par \par \uc2  She said that the Hilton suffered an average occupancy rate of about 25 percent in the May-to-July period. \par \par \uc2  Hotel Mercure Rekso Hayam Wuruk's general manager Tristan Beau de Lomenie echoed Dewi's view. He said that his hotel's occupancy rates was also rising. \par \par \uc2  "As most of our guests are business guests, our monthly occupancy rates were over 40 percent in August and September, improving from around 29 percent in July. This month, we expect the rate to exceed 40 percent," he told the Post. \par \par \uc2  "People are starting to be brave about having big events, such as weddings or business meetings. We have more than two wedding receptions every week." \par \par \uc2  The Regent, Le Meridien, Santika and Kartika Chandra also said their occupancy rates were improving to over 40 percent for the same reasons. \par \par \uc2  "Our monthly occupancy rate actually is over 60 percent since August. It was always about 50 percent in June and July," Kartika Chandra \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  relations manager Dhanny said. \par \par \uc2  But Sari Pan Pacific's director of marketing communications Satria Wira said that his hotel's occupancy rates had stayed flat and that there had been no a significant growth over the last two months. \par \par \uc2  "It is still ranging between 30 percent and 50 percent, and I believe that other hotels are still experiencing the same situation too," he said. \par \par \uc2  Declines \par \par \uc2  The country's hotels have mostly seen drastic declines in their occupancy rates since July last year due to the downturn in tourist arrivals following a series of natural disasters and plane crashes. The May riots in Jakarta, which left hundreds of people dead and led to the resignation of president Soeharto, almost resulted in foreign arrivals drying up altogether. \par \par \uc2  Tourism started to improve in June but \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the political situation still scared off foreigners. \par \par \uc2  Since then, the country's hotels have been facing tight competition due to the lower numbers of foreign visitors and collapse of domestic tourists' purchasing power. \par \par \uc2  Executives of star-rated hotels especially, those based in Jakarta, are still worried about the prospect of the industry within the next three months despite the improving outlook in the last two months. \par \par \uc2  They said that the political situation could worsen again prior to and after the People's Consultative Assembly's (MPR) special meeting in November. \par \par \uc2  The MPR is scheduled to set the schedules of the general election and other political agendas. Dissatisfaction over the result of the meeting could trigger massive street rallies or even unrest. \par \par \uc2  "The prospect is still unclear for the next few months. Business may slump again during the extraordinary session and after that we will enter the Ramadhan fasting season," de Lomenie said, adding that during Ramadhan, which begins in mid-December, the travel and hotel businesses were traditionally bearish. \par \par \uc2  "There will be no business meetings or business activities during the special session. And people do not commonly travel during the fasting month," the Regent's \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  relations manager Nuni Sutyoko-Rasad said. \par \par \uc2  Both de Lomenie and Nuni predicted that occupancy rates would likely pick up again after the Islamic Idul Fitri holiday at the end of the fasting month, providing the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political situation had improved further. (gis) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924duaa000ok\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  The Jakarta bourse gradually recovers. \b0\par\par\uc2  By Richard Nurak. \par \uc2 261 \uc2 words\par \uc2 12 October 1998\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The Jakarta bourse is gradually recovering as it has begun to show positive signals since the middle of last week. \par \par \uc2  The strengthening of the rupiah against the dollar, as it managed to touch the 8.800 level, has made trading at the JSX buoyant again. \par \par \uc2  The smooth PDI Perjuangan congress in Bali also has a positive impact on the Jakarta bourse. \par \par \uc2  The two positive rumors "galvanized" the JSX from a slump. \par \par \uc2  The composite index (IHSG) last week rose by 41.61 points or 15.8% to 304.84 from 263.229. \par \par \uc2  The improved performance of the JSX is inseparable from that of regional currencies, especially the yen, while the government's plan to impose capital flows control and overseas rupiah trading have received positive response from the market. \par \par \uc2  The stronger rupiah against the dollar has also jolted the JSX from a prolonged slump. \par \par \uc2  Since the drop of the Jakarta bourse's index to under the psychological figure of 300 on 15 September, investors' hopes to book gains at the bourse have virtually faded away due to political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Thah hope has now risen last week as losses earlier sustained by investors can now be minimized. \par \par \uc2  Buoyancy on the bourse is expected to continue this week. Signs that The Fed's Allan Greenspan would cut \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  further will encourage investors to seek shares on the Jakarta bourse. \par \par \uc2  However, investors need to beware as the sharp rise of the index will also be followed by profit-taking actions. \par \par \uc2  (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010922duac000tu\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
