\par\par \b \uc2  Rupiah falls on minister's comment. \b0\par\par\uc2 799 \uc2 words\par \uc2 23 October 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): After rallying persistently since the beginning of the month, the rupiah slid back to close at 7,800 against the U.S. dollar on Thursday as the market punished a senior Cabinet minister for commenting that the rupiah should not appreciate too rapidly. \par \par \uc2  Currency dealers attributed Thursday's 9 percent decline in the rupiah mainly to the market's negative response to a controversial statement by Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Finance and Industry Ginandjar Kartasasmita, who on Wednesday said that an ideal range for the rupiah was between 7,000 and 8,000 to maintain the competitiveness of Indonesia's exports. \par \par \uc2  "Although there were several factors affecting the rupiah today, Minister Ginandjar's statement was the dominant factor behind the fall of rupiah," a chief dealer with a local private bank said. \par \par \uc2  He said the fall of the Japanese yen to 117 against the dollar on Thursday was also partially responsible for the rupiah's slide. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah opened strongly at 7,150 to the dollar - exactly the same as Wednesday's close - but then weakened to as low as 7,900 before closing Jakarta trading at 7,800. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah hit an eight month high of 6,950 against the dollar at one point on Wednesday - having improved by almost 50 percent from its level of around 12,000 in September. \par \par \uc2  Currency dealers said that Ginandjar's remark caused massive dollar-buying by offshore operators, especially in Singapore. \par \par \uc2  In an apparent move to stem the rupiah's slide, dealers said, state-banks unloaded dollars for the rupiah but failed to prevent the currency from declining further. \par \par \uc2  Dealers said that some state banks sold dollars for rupiah at exchange rates of 7,200, 7,400, and 7,800. \par \par \uc2  "But massive dollar buying by offshore operators was higher than the value of dollars sold by state banks," the chief dealer said. \par \par \uc2  Ginandjar said on Wednesday that a further appreciation of the rupiah against the dollar would hurt the competitiveness of the country's exports. \par \par \uc2  "I personally expect the rupiah will not strengthen to above the 5,000 level because it will hurt our exports," Ginandjar said. \par \par \uc2  Minister of Industry and Trade Rahardi Ramelan on Thursday dismissed fears that the strengthening rupiah would adversely affect the country's exports. He contended that Indonesian exporters would be flexible in responding to the situation. \par \par \uc2  As the rupiah slid on Thursday, Ginandjar denied any intention on his part to curtail the rupiah's rally against the dollar. \par \par \uc2  "We don't have any intention of curbing the rupiah at that level (7,000), or of stopping it from getting stronger than 7,000," he told journalists on the sidelines of a seminar. \par \par \uc2  He described the weakening of the rupiah on Thursday as a "natural correction" and pointed out that other regional currencies had also fallen in the foreign exchange markets. \par \par \uc2  When Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  fundamentals were improving and regional currencies were also improving, the rupiah rode on the back of that good news, he said. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Director Miranda S. Goeltom said at the same seminar that the rupiah's recent gains were boosted by a declining dollar demand in the market. \par \par \uc2  She said that offshore players, especially from Singapore, actually expected the rupiah to continue to strengthen as exporters began converting their dollar into rupiah. \par \par \uc2  "It is not true if people say that \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  has intervened," she said, adding that a rupiah-dollar exchange rate of between 7,000 and 8,000 would still be competitive for exporters. \par \par \uc2  "There is still room for the rupiah to go to around the 6,500 level as long as there are no external shocks," she said. \par \par \uc2  The year-end target agreed to between the government and the International Monetary Fund (IMF), which arranged a multi-billion dollar bailout fund for Indonesia, is 10,000. \par \par \uc2  The IMF's Asia Pacific director told Dow Jones Newswires in Washington on Thursday that he was encouraged by the rupiah's recent appreciation, but he attributed the rise partly to the Japanese yen's rise against the dollar. \par \par \uc2  Like the rupiah, stock prices on the Jakarta Stock Exchange (JSX) fell 1.7 percent on continued profit taking after strong gains recently. \par \par \uc2  The JSX Composite Index closed 5.52 points down at 316.79 on a total turnover of 204.88 million shares valued at Rp 172.53 billion. \par \par \uc2  Losers beat gainers by 47 to 37 with 92 stocks ending the day unchanged. \par \par \uc2  The head of research at BNI Securities, Adrian Rusmana, said a weaker rupiah coupled with lingering \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the domestic political environment had killed market sentiment. \par \par \uc2  "I think profit taking and lingering worries over the country's political situation capped investors' buying sentiment," he said. (aly) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924duan002qy\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
