\par\par \b \uc2  Bank recapitalization program to go ahead. \b0\par\par\uc2 393 \uc2 words\par \uc2 10 November 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  8 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Governor Sjahril Sabirin stressed on Monday that the government would not delay its bank recapitalization program despite bankers' protests. \par \par \uc2  He said that bank owners should make a "great effort" to come up with fresh money to finance at least 20 percent of the recapitalization program. \par \par \uc2  "We have to make a great effort to implement the bank recapitalization program as scheduled," he told reporters following a meeting with several \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  ministers. \par \par \uc2  The government has required all of the country's commercial banks to have a minimum capital adequacy ratio (CAR) of 4 percent by the end of this year, 8 percent by the end of 1999, and 10 percent by the end of 2000. \par \par \uc2  CAR is the ratio between equity capital and risk-weighted assets. \par \par \uc2  Under the recapitalization program, the government will provide 80 percent of the required funding. \par \par \uc2  Banks which are qualified to join the recapitalization program are those which have a CAR of between minus 25 percent and plus 4 percent. \par \par \uc2  Banks outside the above category have to inject fresh capital or improve their nonperforming assets to raise the CAR level to the meet qualifying standard. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  has recently completed financial audits of most of the country's more than 200 commercial banks. \par \par \uc2  Sjahril has said that most of the banks have an acute capital deficiency condition but were qualified to join the recapitalization program. \par \par \uc2  Bankers last week expressed objections to the recapitalization program, citing difficulties in raising enough cash amid the current tight liquidity conditions. \par \par \uc2  The chairman of the Association of Indonesian Private Commercial Banks, Gunarni Soeworo, said that it would be arduous for bankers even to only come up with 20 percent of the financing requirement. \par \par \uc2  She added that inviting foreign investors to enter the banking sector would be hard because of \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the country's political situation. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  officials had urged cash-strapped bankers to invite foreign investors to help finance the recapitalization program. \par \par \uc2  The government has revised the country's banking law, which allows 100 percent of foreign ownership in the banking industry. \par \par \uc2  Bankers also proposed that fixed assets be used for financing the recapitalization program. This was rejected by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "We want cash. Without it what's the use of recapitalization," Sjahril said last week. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924duba0017w\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
