\par\par \b \uc2  RI's  \highlight22\uc2 economy \highlight\uc2  to start growing in 2000 - Mari. \b0\par\par\uc2 582 \uc2 words\par \uc2 3 December 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  10 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Fallout from domestic political turmoil rules out the country returning to the growth track before 2000, noted economist Mari E. Pangestu said on Wednesday. \par \par \uc2  The executive director of the Center for Strategic and International Studies added that the country would record negative growth next year of between minus 2 percent and minus 5 percent. \par \par \uc2  "As we have to balance social and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  concerns, our recovery will be very slow. We need at least three to four years to reach a normal situation, that is growth of 6 percent per annum," she said at a year-end news conference. \par \par \uc2  Mari used the occasion to bid farewell to journalists as she will join her husband in the U.S. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery in Indonesia will depend heavily on inflow of private capital but it would not come during a crisis, she said. \par \par \uc2  "We are experiencing a crisis in leadership - a crisis in political leadership, a crisis in \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  leadership and a crisis in military leadership." \par \par \uc2  Even if all political plans go according to schedule, real private investment will not enter Indonesia until a new government is formed by the end of 1999. \par \par \uc2  Prospective foreign investors prioritize \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  consistency and credibility of a new government in making their choices, Mari said. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  consistency would not be a major issue in the near future because Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would still be steered by the International Monetary Fund, which arranged a multibillion dollar bailout for the country. \par \par \uc2  In terms of government credibility, Mari said foreign investors would act on cues from domestic investors. Once domestic investors started to invest, foreign investors would follow suit. \par \par \uc2  Mari acknowledged that Indonesia's macroeconomic health was improving, with falling \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  and inflation and a steady rupiah. \par \par \uc2  "But that could not yet serve as a foundation for growth as there are still great \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the real, financial and political sectors." \par \par \uc2  Mari believed inflation would fall next year, but it would still be in double digits and higher than the government's target of between 10 percent and 15 percent. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah exchange rate would remain stable at the current level or even strengthen toward March 1999, the end of this \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year, because official funds would continue to flow in. \par \par \uc2  She warned that rupiah stability would be in danger once corporations started to repay their loans. \par \par \uc2  The currency has stabilized in very thin trading on the foreign exchange market. Once large demand arises, Mari cautioned that the local unit would be easily pushed down. \par \par \uc2  "Therefore, it is very important to solve this private debt hangover." \par \par \uc2  Indonesia's private corporations owe more than US$60 billion to foreign creditors. \par \par \uc2  Economist Pande Raja Silalahi said the problem of foreign exchange would continue to loom in the immediate future because the government would still need about $10 billion to $14 billion in foreign aid next \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year to finance deficits in the State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  It will not be easy for the government to get that amount as it has drained a huge amount of creditors' money this year. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  from State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  will become a prime mover of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activities next year because bank lending would still minimal. \par \par \uc2  Pande contended that most of third party funds in the country's banking industry were short-term at less than one-month duration. \par \par \uc2  "Therefore, it is of the utmost important to restore \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  trust in the banking system." (rid) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924duc3001vk\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  RAPBN 1999/2000 may put  \highlight22\uc2 deficit \highlight\uc2  at 6% of GDP. \b0\par\par\uc2 392 \uc2 words\par \uc2 11 December 1998\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The government has set a \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  figure of 6% of the GDP in the RAPBN (draft state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 )1999/2000 in order to underwrite the social safety net program (JPS). \par \par \uc2  A Bisnis source said the size of the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  is not unlike that of the current \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  as the government may have to pay for JPS programs due to social, \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  next year. \par \par \uc2  He said the government would not be able to reduce drastically the \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the new \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The current \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  of 1998/1999 has set a figure of 8.5% of the GDP, but was revised to 6%. \par \par \uc2  "A lower figure of, say under 5%, is impossible as the social safety net programs require huge funds," he said. \par \par \uc2  However, the government could also not afford a figure higher than 8% as that would undermine the macro-\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  condition of Indonesia and her national development. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  is expected to be covered by foreign aid whose size is slightly lower than loans Indonesia received in the 1998/1999 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The 1998/1999 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  saw Indonesia getting foreign aid worth about US$14 billion originating from CGI (US$7.9 billion) and the IMF (US$6.2 billion). \par \par \uc2  The government has tentatively targeted foreign aid at US$6,3 billion in the RAPBN 1999/2000, coming from the World Bank, the ADB, the OECF and the Miyazawa Plan of Japan. \par \par \uc2  From the Miyazawa Plan, the government envisions getting US$3 billion, half of which will be used for JPS programs. \par \par \uc2  He predicted that Indonesia would still be needing huge external financing as her \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is still recovering. \par \par \uc2  The JPS program, according to Bappenas chief Boediono, covers 17 development sectors worth Rp17.99 trillion or 55.5% of development \b \highlight22\uc2 expenditure\b0 \highlight\uc2  in rupiah. \par \par \uc2  The figure is higher than the earlier amount of Rp17.25 trillion as there had been changes such as increased aid for the regions. \par \par \uc2  Boediono said that the JPS places emphasis on food security, which is securing the people's need for essential goods at affordable prices through \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The programs also hope to create wide employment possibilities and "create purchasing power among the poor so that they would be able have access to essential needs," said Boediono. (msw). \par \par \uc2  (c) 1998 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010922ducb001a5\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
