\par\par \b \uc2  The crisis  \highlight22\uc2 budget \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 777 \uc2 words\par \uc2 15 December 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  4 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  The 1999/2000 State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  starting in April will remain a crisis-\b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  program albeit to a lesser degree than the current one. The bulk of the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  will still go to routine operating expenditures and social safety-net programs. The massive bank restructuring and preparations for, and holding of, the general election in June will take up another sizable piece of the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , leaving a tiny portion for investment (development). \par \par \uc2  Also similar to the current \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the next one will be heavily influenced by politics, notably the \b \highlight22\uc2 legislative\b0 \highlight\uc2  election in early June and presidential election in November. \par \par \uc2  However, preparations for the next \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  seem to be much better and based on more realistic assumptions, unlike the present one which had to be revised several times because of the arrogance on the part of the now bygone Soeharto administration, which stubbornly refused to acknowledge and factor in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis in its \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  plan. \par \par \uc2  More encouraging to note is what is likely to be the first real sign of greater transparency in the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 -making process. For the first time in over 30 years, the government publicly announced most of the key assumptions used for its \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  proposal more than five weeks before it will be unveiled to the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Under Soeharto's New Order administration, such key indicators were disclosed only when the President revealed the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  proposal to the House in the first week of January. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  assumptions for the next State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , as announced by finance minister Bambang Subianto last week, appear to be fairly realistic. The rupiah's exchange rate is envisaged at an average 7,500 to the dollar, up from the 9,500 average for the current \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year. Inflation is projected at between 15 percent and 20 percent, down from more than 76 percent this year, and the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  at 6 percent of the gross domestic product, against 8.5 percent in the current \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year. International oil prices are projected at a range of $11.50 to 12.50/barrel. \par \par \uc2  Gross domestic product growth is projected around plus or minus 1 percent, meaning that \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  activities will expand by a range of 14 percent to 16 percent from the drastic shrinkage of about 15 percent predicted this calendar year. \par \par \uc2  Another development which will be a great boon to the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is projected \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  of between 20 percent and 30 percent, down sharply from as high as 70 percent in September and 38 percent last week. It will go a long way in greasing the wheels of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , especially because bank lending, virtually at a standstill now, will likely resume soon after the completion of the bank recapitalization program scheduled for the end of March. \par \par \uc2  As private investments will likely remain on hold at least until the appointment of a new administration later next year, and while the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  sector, preoccupied with its contingency-\b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  plan, cannot make any meaningful investment, bank lending then will become the main source of the lifeblood - liquidity - to the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . It was therefore not an exaggeration for the finance minister, the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's governor and the chief \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  minister to assert last week that the bank recapitalization program is crucial for \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery. \par \par \uc2  Progress in the settlement, or rather the restructuring, of the huge corporate foreign debt will be vital for keeping the rupiah stable around the current levels of 7,400-7,500. A stable rupiah is in turn a key to sound \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  planning. \par \par \uc2  Though the stronger rupiah will help decrease price \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  for such imported commodities as rice, soybeans and fuel, the 1999/2000 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  will still be much larger than the current one to cover \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  for broader social safety net programs, interest rate \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  for credits to farmers and small firms, the costs of bank restructuring and preparations and holding of the general election. A likely increase of at least 20 percent in the salaries of civil servants and members of the Armed Forces, though negligible in real terms in view of the more than 76 percent inflation this year, will add significantly to the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  As revenues will, at best, remain stagnant, the coming state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , like its predecessor, will depend largely on international aid funds, notably those from the International Monetary Fund, World Bank and Asian Development Fund and Japan. \par \par \uc2  However realistic and conservative the assumptions seem to be, the biggest pitfall to all the estimates lies in the political field. \b \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the run-up to \b \highlight22\uc2 legislative\b0 \highlight\uc2  elections is still highly likely, a factor which ultimately keeps investors clear of the country. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924ducf002af\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
