\par\par \b \uc2  City's New Year's celebrations  \highlight22\uc2 uncertain \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 485 \uc2 words\par \uc2 16 December 1998\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  3 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1998 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): A gubernatorial decree concerning \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  celebrations on New Year's Eve is still in the works, but councilors were split on Tuesday on whether the show should go on to bring in 1999. \par \par \uc2  Head of the United Development Party (PPP) faction, Achmad Suaidy, demanded that Governor Sutiyoso ban all \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  festivities due to the unstable security situation, with the exception of celebrations organized at star-rated hotels. \par \par \uc2  He argued the ban would also meet calls of several Moslem groups which said celebrations would be improper in the middle of the Ramadhan fasting month. \par \par \uc2  Fresh unrest could break out if the governor failed to heed his advice, Suaidy warned. \par \par \uc2  Star-rated hotels would be excluded "as they're part of the international community". \par \par \uc2  Dissenting opinions were voiced by the respective heads of the Indonesian Democratic Party (PDI) faction, Lukman Mokoginta, and the Armed Forces (ABRI), Sumekar. \par \par \uc2  They said New Year's celebrations should be held at recreation sites, such as the Ancol Dreamworld in North Jakarta and Taman Mini Indonesia Indah park in East Jakarta, albeit with restrictions. \par \par \uc2  The governor could limit the party hours and order all organizers to mark the event in a modest way. \par \par \uc2  The city administration should accommodate Jakartans who want to celebrate the date, including with adequate provision of security, Lukman said. \par \par \uc2  "The authorities should prepare a strong security troop (deployment) to anticipate any possibilities." \par \par \uc2  Last year, the administration banned hotels, discotheques, cafes and nightclubs from holding New Year's celebrations because the date coincided with the opening of the fasting month. \par \par \uc2  Deputy Governor for Administrative Affairs Abdul Kahfi told reporters on Tuesday the city administration was still preparing a gubernatorial decree on celebrations. \par \par \uc2  Suaidy said he feared irresponsible parties would use \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  celebrations to foment unrest. \par \par \uc2  "That's why it is better that events like fireworks displays are banned." \par \par \uc2  Several enterprises contacted by The Jakarta Post on Tuesday said they had already decided to hold low-key celebrations. \par \par \uc2  Dede Rusli, \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  relations manager of Champions bar and restaurant in Kemang, South Jakarta, said no special events were planned for New Year's Eve. \par \par \uc2  "There will only be musical performances by our home band. We have no plan, for instance, to present famous singers like in previous years." \par \par \uc2  Nuni Sutyoko Rasad, \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  relations manager of Regent Hotel in South Jakarta, said: "I think people won't be looking for glamorous parties this year (due to the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis), that's why we also have no special event for New Year's Eve. \par \par \uc2  "We are only offering special dinners at our three restaurants." \par \par \uc2  Marketing officer of South Jakarta's Galeri TC cafe, Ade Sri Purwaningsih, said this year would be no different than the previous New Year's Eve. \par \par \uc2  "We'll have no special events, like last year's New Year Eve, out of respect for Ramadhan." (ind) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1998 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010924ducg002cq\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
